<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFE2FFC9FF6BFF3AFEA1FD23" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE2FFC9FF6BFF3AFE15FEE3" blockId="56.[151,1127,220,691]" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FF6BFF3AFEB8FF43" bold="true" box="[151,262,220,243]" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">Remarks.</emphasis>
Describing 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FE74FF3AFC9EFF43" authority=", ERICHSON (1847)" authorityName=", ERICHSON" authorityYear="1847" box="[392,800,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruentata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FE74FF3AFDDFFF43" box="[392,609,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">Cyrtonota cruentata</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE2FFC9FD93FF3AFC9EFF43" author="ERICHSON" box="[623,800,220,243]" firstAuthor="ERICHSON" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" pagination="67 - 185" refId="ref49195" refString="ERICHSON G. F. 1847: Conspectus insectorum coleopterorum, quae in republica Peruana observata sunt. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 30: 67 - 185." type="journal article" year="1847">ERICHSON (1847)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
did not state how many specimens he had at his disposal. However, he mentioned a single length measurement and also according to the ZMHB register number there was only a single specimen hence considered as 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE2FFC9FF48FEDAFEAFFEE3" box="[180,273,316,339]" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">holotype</typeStatus>
by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE2FFC9FF49FEBAFEA1FD23" blockId="56.[151,1127,220,691]" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE2FFC9FF49FEBAFEDCFEC3" author="BOHEMAN" box="[181,354,348,371]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" refId="ref47980" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1857: Catalogue of Coleopterous Insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part IX. Cassidae. Printed by Order of the trustees [of the British Museum], London, 225 pp." type="book" year="1857">BOHEMAN (1857)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FE33FEBAFD4BFEC3" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[463,757,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deplorabunda">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FE33FEBAFD4BFEC3" box="[463,757,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">Mesomphalia deplorabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presumably from a single specimen as he gave a single length measurement and did not indicate any specimen in his collection (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE2FFC9FF63FE7AFEFAFE03" author="BOHEMAN" box="[159,324,412,435]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">BOHEMAN 1862</bibRefCitation>
). This taxon was enigmatic to subsequent authors and was listed only in catalogues and 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE2FFC9FED8FE5AFE02FE63" author="SPAETH" box="[292,444,444,467]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FD92FE5AFCF5FE63" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1901" box="[622,843,444,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudomesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FD92FE5AFCF5FE63" box="[622,843,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">Pseudomesomphalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FC8DFE5AFC0CFE63" baseAuthorityName="BOROWIEC" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[881,946,444,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FC8DFE5AFC0CFE63" box="[881,946,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">Stolas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In my opinion, the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE2FFC9FF3CFE3AFEA3FE43" box="[192,285,476,499]" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FEBFFE3AFE4AFE43" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[323,500,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deplorabunda">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FEBFFE3AFE4AFE43" box="[323,500,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">S. deplorabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only a uniformly black specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FC62FE3AFB9EFE43" authorityName=", ERICHSON" authorityYear="1847" box="[926,1056,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruentata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FC62FE3AFB9EFE43" box="[926,1056,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">S. cruentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the two taxa are nearly identical besides colouration. Typical 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FD01FE1AFCC3FDA3" authorityName=", ERICHSON" authorityYear="1847" box="[765,893,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruentata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FD01FE1AFCC3FDA3" box="[765,893,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">S. cruentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a red and slightly elevated reticulation on elytra. This reticulation is structurally also present in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FC45FDFAFBD9FD83" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[953,1127,540,563]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deplorabunda">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FC45FDFAFBD9FD83" box="[953,1127,540,563]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">S. deplorabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is black and its punctation appears slightly coarser than in typical 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FC8EFDDAFC4FFDE3" authorityName=", ERICHSON" authorityYear="1847" box="[882,1009,572,595]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruentata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FC8EFDDAFC4FFDE3" box="[882,1009,572,595]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">S. cruentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I consider these differences as intraspecific variability and hereby synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FC81FDBAFB91FDC3" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[893,1071,604,627]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deplorabunda">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FC81FDBAFB91FDC3" box="[893,1071,604,627]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">S. deplorabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE2FFC9FF6BFD9AFEA6FD23" authorityName=", ERICHSON" authorityYear="1847" box="[151,280,636,659]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruentata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE2FFC9FF6BFD9AFEA6FD23" box="[151,280,636,659]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="331">S. cruentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
